column8: Over voltage: The input voltage of the external power system exceeds the upper limit.  Under voltage: The input voltage of the external power system is below the lower limit.Possible causes include: insufficient electricity supply,air switch is not enough,the diameter of power cable is not enough,the length of power cable is too long. Power-down: The input voltage of the external power supply system is interrupted. Insufficient power supply capacity: The external power supply equipment or batteries do not have a sufficient load-carrying capacity, resulting in an alarm of insufficient power supply capacity due to an under-voltage-related calibration failure. The possible reasons are insufficient mains electricity supply,a low air circuit breaker capacity,a small power cable diameter,and a too long power cable.
